  "body": "### Question\r\nI attempted to query an older transaction from Jul-12-2017 01:57:47 PM +UTC, but 'geth' returned null, which strikes me as odd. [Here is the link to the transaction on etherscan.io](https://etherscan.io/tx/0xb31f87312b1131e9fe8344f2b21be8d3deed73a4ac218e6a25912b0481888cee).\r\n\r\nThe command I used was:\r\n\r\n```\r\ncurl -X POST -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" --data '{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"method\":\"eth_getTransactionByHash\",\"params\":[\"0xb31f87312b1131e9fe8344f2b21be8d3deed73a4ac218e6a25912b0481888cee\"],\"id\":1}' http://localhost:8599\r\nAnd the response received was:\r\n\r\n{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"id\":1,\"result\":null}\r\n```\r\nMy Geth version is v1.13.4. Here are the startup parameters:\r\n```\r\ngeth -\r\n-authrpc.jwtsecret=/secret/jwtsecret \r\n--authrpc.addr=0.0.0.0 \r\n--authrpc.port=8551\r\n--authrpc.vhosts=* \r\n--http\r\n--http.addr=0.0.0.0 \r\n--http.port=8599 \r\n--http.vhosts=* \r\n--http.api=web3,eth,net,engine,debug \r\n--datadir=/data/ethereum  \r\n--mainnet \r\n--syncmode=snap\r\n--db.engine=leveldb\r\n--txlookuplimit=0\r\n```",
